### v0.4.4 master ontology TTL.
### =====================================================================

@prefix owl:   <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf:   <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs:  <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd:   <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .
@prefix skos:  <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#> .
@prefix sh:    <http://www.w3.org/ns/shacl#> .
@prefix gist:  <https://ontologies.semanticarts.com/gist/> .
@prefix canon: <https://canonmanagement.io/vocab/cmmc/> .
@prefix cmmc:  <http://canonmanagement.io/cmmc/ontology#> .

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### DELTA REPORT (v0.4.3 → v0.4.4)
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### New classes (4):
###   - cmmc:LoopArtifact         rdfs:subClassOf gist:Commitment
###       (covering concept: a future-state obligation produced by an Eight
###        Verb Loop pass; queue-shaped work the system commits to surface)
###   - cmmc:MorningReviewItem    rdfs:subClassOf cmmc:LoopArtifact
###   - cmmc:Routine              rdfs:subClassOf gist:Behavior
###       (covering concept: a recurring scheduled-task agent; named
###        individuals are the canonical loop-1, loop-2, manual routines)
###   - cmmc:ControlObjective     rdfs:subClassOf gist:Commitment
###       (covering concept: a single assessment objective derived from a
###        NIST SP 800-171 Control; finer-grained than cmmc:Control)
###
### New object properties (3):
###   - cmmc:concerns      (domain MorningReviewItem;
###                          range owl:unionOf {Engagement, Control,
###                                             owl:Ontology, ControlObjective})
###   - cmmc:proposedBy    (domain MorningReviewItem; range Routine)
###   - cmmc:resolvedBy    (domain MorningReviewItem; range Affirmation)
###
### New datatype properties (8):
###   - cmmc:itemId        xsd:string  (functional)
###   - cmmc:proposedAt    xsd:dateTime (functional)
###   - cmmc:gapKind       xsd:string with controlled vocabulary (5 values)
###   - cmmc:targetGraph   xsd:string  (canon-mgmt | <engagementId>)
###   - cmmc:summary       xsd:string
###   - cmmc:payload       xsd:string  (JSON literal, kind-specific shape)
###   - cmmc:status        xsd:string with controlled vocabulary (FSM, 4 values)
###   - cmmc:missingFields xsd:string  (parsed from payload by gapKind=missing-data)
###
### New named individuals (3):
###   - cmmc:Routine-Loop1   a cmmc:Routine
###   - cmmc:Routine-Loop2   a cmmc:Routine
###   - cmmc:Routine-Manual  a cmmc:Routine
###
### New SKOS schemes (2):
###   - cmmc:GapKindScheme        — 5 concepts (forward-compat, McComb-aligned)
###   - cmmc:MorningReviewStatusScheme — 4 concepts (FSM canonical labels)
###
### New invariants (3):
###   - cmmc:Invariant17-MorningReviewFSM
###   - cmmc:Invariant18-MissingDataRequiresMissingFields
###   - cmmc:Invariant19-MorningReviewItemDefaultPending
###
### New SHACL NodeShape (1):
###   - cmmc:MorningReviewItemShape — encodes FSM membership + missing-data rule
###
### Conflicts with existing ontology (v0.4.3): none.
###   - cmmc:Affirmation already exists (declared at v0.4.3 line 294); reused as
###     range of cmmc:resolvedBy. No re-declaration.
###   - cmmc:Engagement and cmmc:Control already exist; reused as union members
###     of cmmc:concerns range. No re-declaration.
###   - owl:Ontology is the standard OWL class for ontology individuals; the
###     v0.4.3 master is itself an owl:Ontology. Reused as a union member of
###     cmmc:concerns range; no cmmc:Ontology class minted (covering concept
###     already exists upstream — McComb principle 3).
###   - cmmc:Invariant class minted in v0.4.3 merge; reused for the three
###     new Invariant individuals.
###
### McComb principles applied:
###   (1) Data is permanent, applications are ephemeral — the queue schema is
###       designed to outlive the Phase 2 MCP server that writes to it.
###   (3) Use gist primitives as covering concepts — LoopArtifact, Routine,
###       and ControlObjective all subclass through gist; owl:Ontology reused.
###   (4) Commitments and Resources as core — the queue item is a Commitment
###       (a future-tense obligation to review); state changes (pending →
###       approved → executed) are property updates, not separate Event classes.
###   (5) Separate ontology from taxonomy — gapKind and status are SKOS
###       concept schemes (instances) layered alongside xsd:string properties
###       with owl:oneOf datatype enums; FSM transitions enforced via SHACL,
###       not OWL classes per state.
###   (7) Invariants are the enforcement layer — the FSM, the default-pending
###       rule, and the missing-data → missingFields rule are all stated as
###       cmmc:Invariant instances AND as a SHACL NodeShape.
###
### Vocabulary discipline (Phase 0 canon, Session 10):
###   - Use "CMMC Level 1/2/3" in prose. Never "L1/L2/L3".
###   - "Routine" (capital R) = scheduled-task agent (this ontology's class).
###     Distinct from OpenClaw cron jobs; the canon term is reserved.
###   - "MorningReviewItem" is the canonical Neo4j label (Session 10 freeze).
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------

### =====================================================================
### 1. NEW CLASSES
### =====================================================================

### ---- cmmc:LoopArtifact ------------------------------------------------
### Covering concept: gist:Commitment (a future-state obligation produced by
### a pass of the Eight Verb Loop — work the system commits to surface for
### review, approval, or execution).
### McComb principle: ~80% of business activity is the making and fulfilling
### of obligations. A LoopArtifact is the system's record of an obligation
### created by a Loop pass. Subclasses formalize the kind of work surfaced.
### Origin: Phase 0 Session 10 — runtime needs a queue substrate above the
### ontology that is itself an artifact of the Loop, not part of the
### compliance domain proper. LoopArtifact is the parent for any future
### queue/work-item classes (e.g. EveningCloseoutItem, AdHocReviewItem).

cmmc:LoopArtifact a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf gist:Commitment ;            ### gist check: subclass of gist:Commitment — future-state work obligation surfaced by the Loop ✓
    rdfs:label "Loop Artifact"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "An obligation produced by a single pass of the Eight Verb Loop (Elicit → Taxonomize → Canonize → Ontogize → Knowledge Graph → Traverse → Simulate → Enforce). LoopArtifacts are queue items the runtime commits to surface for human review or downstream automation. Subclasses formalize the kind of work surfaced; this parent class lets the runtime treat all such artifacts uniformly without conflating them with compliance-domain obligations such as ContractObligation."@en ;
    skos:exactMatch canon:LoopArtifact .
    ### Layer 3X (runtime/build extension): not part of the CMMC compliance
    ### domain proper. Distinguishes work the system surfaces ABOUT the
    ### domain from obligations IN the domain.

### ---- cmmc:MorningReviewItem ------------------------------------------
### Covering concept: gist:Commitment via cmmc:LoopArtifact.
### Phase 1 anchor class. Each instance is one row in the morning-review
### queue surfaced to the user (Dalaun) by Loop 1 (overnight pass) or
### Loop 2 (weekly pass), or filed manually. Status FSM:
###     pending → approved | rejected
###     approved → executed
### No backward transitions. Default at creation is "pending". See
### cmmc:Invariant17-MorningReviewFSM, cmmc:Invariant19-MorningReviewItemDefaultPending,
### and cmmc:MorningReviewItemShape (SHACL).

cmmc:MorningReviewItem a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf cmmc:LoopArtifact ;          ### gist check: subclass of gist:Commitment via LoopArtifact ✓
    rdfs:label "Morning Review Item"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "A single row in the morning-review queue surfaced by the runtime to the human reviewer. Each MorningReviewItem represents a gap or proposal that the Eight Verb Loop has detected and that requires human approval before downstream automation acts. Canonical Neo4j label (locked in Session 10 Phase 0): MorningReviewItem. Created by Routine instances (loop-1, loop-2, manual). Resolved by attaching an Affirmation when status transitions to executed."@en ;
    skos:exactMatch canon:MorningReviewItem .

### ---- cmmc:Routine -----------------------------------------------------
### Covering concept: gist:Behavior (a recurring pattern of activity
### scheduled to fire on a defined cadence; the agent that proposes
### LoopArtifacts).
### McComb principle: Reuse of broad gist primitives. A Routine is not a
### Person, not an Organization, not an Event; it is the Behavior pattern
### that emits queue items.
### Naming distinction (Session 10 canon): Routines (capital R) are scheduled
### tasks that produce LoopArtifacts. Distinct from OpenClaw cron jobs
### (which are infrastructure plumbing). Three named individuals minted
### below cover the Phase 1 design space.

cmmc:Routine a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf gist:Behavior ;              ### gist check: subclass of gist:Behavior — recurring scheduled-task agent ✓
    rdfs:label "Routine"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "A recurring, scheduled-task agent that proposes LoopArtifacts. Routines are not the items themselves; they are the Behavior pattern that surfaces items. Phase 1 defines three canonical individuals: loop-1 (overnight pass), loop-2 (weekly pass), manual (human-filed item). Future routines may include loop-3 (monthly pass) or domain-specific scanners."@en ;
    skos:exactMatch canon:Routine .

### ---- cmmc:ControlObjective -------------------------------------------
### Covering concept: gist:Commitment (a single assessment objective
### derived from a NIST SP 800-171 Control; finer-grained than the parent
### Control, which itself is a Commitment).
### Origin: a MorningReviewItem may concern a single ControlObjective
### (e.g. AC.L2-3.1.1.a) rather than the whole Control (AC.L2-3.1.1).
### NIST SP 800-171A defines assessment objectives a/b/c per control.

cmmc:ControlObjective a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf gist:Commitment ;            ### gist check: subclass of gist:Commitment — finer-grained than Control ✓
    rdfs:label "Control Objective"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "A single assessment objective derived from a NIST SP 800-171A control. NIST SP 800-171A decomposes each Control into one or more assessment objectives (typically labeled a, b, c, ...). Cited by identifier patterns such as AC.L2-3.1.1.a. ControlObjective is the finest-grained obligation unit in the CMMC compliance domain; many findings, oversight requirements, and remediation tasks attach at the objective level rather than the Control level."@en ;
    skos:exactMatch canon:ControlObjective .

### =====================================================================
### 2. NEW OBJECT PROPERTIES
### =====================================================================

### ---- cmmc:concerns ---------------------------------------------------
### Domain: MorningReviewItem.
### Range: owl:unionOf { cmmc:Engagement, cmmc:Control,
###                      owl:Ontology, cmmc:ControlObjective }.
### McComb tradeoff acknowledged: McComb advises broad properties without
### strict ranges (gist principle). Here the prompt prescribes a union to
### keep downstream consumers (the Phase 2 MCP server) able to constrain
### what concerns can point at. The union is the narrowest range that
### still admits the four concrete subject kinds enumerated in the
### Phase 1 design memory.

cmmc:concerns a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range [
        a owl:Class ;
        owl:unionOf ( cmmc:Engagement cmmc:Control owl:Ontology cmmc:ControlObjective )
    ] ;
    rdfs:label "Concerns"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a MorningReviewItem to the subject of the gap or proposal. Range is restricted to the four canonical subject kinds: an Engagement (the gap is data missing from a specific engagement), a Control (the gap concerns a NIST control's representation), an Ontology (the gap is an ontology delta — a missing class, property, or invariant), or a ControlObjective (the gap is at the assessment-objective grain). Multi-valued: an item may concern multiple subjects (e.g. an Engagement and the specific Control it failed)."@en ;
    skos:exactMatch canon:concerns .

### ---- cmmc:proposedBy -------------------------------------------------
### Domain: MorningReviewItem. Range: Routine.

cmmc:proposedBy a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range cmmc:Routine ;
    rdfs:label "Proposed By"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Identifies the Routine that surfaced this MorningReviewItem. Functional in practice (each item has exactly one proposing Routine) but not declared owl:FunctionalProperty here to allow future composite-routine scenarios. The three canonical proposing Routine individuals are cmmc:Routine-Loop1, cmmc:Routine-Loop2, and cmmc:Routine-Manual."@en ;
    skos:exactMatch canon:proposedBy .

### ---- cmmc:resolvedBy -------------------------------------------------
### Domain: MorningReviewItem. Range: Affirmation (already exists in v0.4.3).

cmmc:resolvedBy a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range cmmc:Affirmation ;
    rdfs:label "Resolved By"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Links a MorningReviewItem to the Affirmation produced when the item is approved and executed. Present only when status='executed'. Provides the evidence trail from a runtime queue decision back to the Affirmation record (which itself sits in the compliance domain proper). The Affirmation captures the human approver, decision timestamp, and the action taken."@en ;
    skos:exactMatch canon:resolvedBy .

### =====================================================================
### 3. NEW DATATYPE PROPERTIES
### =====================================================================

cmmc:itemId a owl:DatatypeProperty , owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Item Id"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Globally unique identifier for the MorningReviewItem. Convention: UUID v7 string (time-ordered) so insertion order is recoverable from the ID. Functional — exactly one itemId per item."@en .

cmmc:proposedAt a owl:DatatypeProperty , owl:FunctionalProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:dateTime ;
    rdfs:label "Proposed At"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Wall-clock timestamp at which the proposing Routine emitted the item. ISO 8601, timezone-aware. Functional. The runtime sorts the morning queue by this value ascending."@en .

cmmc:gapKind a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Gap Kind"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "The kind of gap or proposal this item represents. Five canonical values managed as a SKOS concept scheme (cmmc:GapKindScheme): 'missing-data' (an Engagement is missing data the runtime cannot self-fill), 'ontology-delta' (the ontology lacks a needed class/property/invariant), 'harness-delta' (the runtime harness needs a code/config change), 'elicitation-question' (a human SME needs to answer a question before the Loop can advance), 'gate-state-change' (a gate query result has flipped). String-typed for Neo4j round-trip simplicity; the SKOS scheme provides the governance surface (per McComb principle 5)."@en .

### Constrain enum values with owl:oneOf on an anonymous datatype.
### SHACL provides the runtime constraint; this aids reasoner inference.
_:gapKindValueSet a rdfs:Datatype ;
    owl:equivalentClass [
        a rdfs:Datatype ;
        owl:oneOf ( "missing-data" "ontology-delta" "harness-delta"
                    "elicitation-question" "gate-state-change" )
    ] .

cmmc:targetGraph a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Target Graph"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Identifier of the Neo4j graph context the item refers to. Two patterns: 'canon-mgmt' (Canon Management's own self-assessment graph, shared substrate) or '<engagementId>' (e.g. 'ENG-2026-MERIDIAN-001' — a specific client engagement subgraph). Disambiguates items that concern the same Control or ControlObjective across multiple engagements."@en .

cmmc:summary a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Summary"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "One-line, human-readable summary of the gap or proposal. Rendered in the WhatsApp morning-review digest emitted by Routine A. Should be terse and decision-supporting (e.g. 'ENG-2026-CANON-001 missing assessedSPRSScore — needs SME elicitation')."@en .

cmmc:payload a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Payload"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Kind-specific structured data, serialized as a JSON literal. Schema varies by gapKind: for 'missing-data', payload MUST contain a non-empty 'missingFields' array (see cmmc:Invariant18-MissingDataRequiresMissingFields). For 'ontology-delta', payload describes proposed class/property additions. For 'harness-delta', payload references the affected code path. For 'elicitation-question', payload contains the question text and proposed SME target. For 'gate-state-change', payload captures before/after gate values."@en .

cmmc:status a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Status"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Position of this item in the morning-review FSM. Four canonical values (cmmc:MorningReviewStatusScheme): 'pending' (default at creation; awaiting human review), 'approved' (human approved the proposal but action has not yet executed), 'rejected' (human declined; terminal state), 'executed' (action taken; an Affirmation is attached via cmmc:resolvedBy; terminal state). FSM enforced by cmmc:Invariant17-MorningReviewFSM and the SHACL shape cmmc:MorningReviewItemShape."@en .

### Constrain enum values with owl:oneOf on an anonymous datatype.
_:statusValueSet a rdfs:Datatype ;
    owl:equivalentClass [
        a rdfs:Datatype ;
        owl:oneOf ( "pending" "approved" "rejected" "executed" )
    ] .

cmmc:missingFields a owl:DatatypeProperty ;
    rdfs:domain cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;
    rdfs:range xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "Missing Fields"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Convenience denormalization of the missingFields array embedded in payload, when gapKind='missing-data'. One literal per missing field name (e.g. 'assessedSPRSScore', 'priorSPRSScore'). Mandatory and non-empty when gapKind='missing-data' (see cmmc:Invariant18). Optional otherwise. Lets Cypher queries filter on missing fields without parsing JSON."@en .

### =====================================================================
### 4. NAMED INDIVIDUALS — CANONICAL ROUTINES
### =====================================================================

cmmc:Routine-Loop1 a cmmc:Routine ;
    rdfs:label "Routine: Loop 1 (overnight pass)"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Overnight Loop 1 routine. Scans the cmmc graph for missing-data, ontology-delta, and gate-state-change gaps. First scheduled fire was 2026-04-26 07:00 America/Chicago via /etc/cron.d/cmmc-gate-health on the VPS (Phase 0 Routine A scaffolding). Phase 3 will extend this routine to emit MorningReviewItem nodes for every detected gap."@en ;
    skos:notation "loop-1" .

cmmc:Routine-Loop2 a cmmc:Routine ;
    rdfs:label "Routine: Loop 2 (weekly pass)"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Weekly Loop 2 routine. Performs deeper traversal-and-simulation passes whose results are too expensive to run nightly. Surfaces harness-delta and elicitation-question items. Scheduled cadence: weekly, day to be determined in Phase 3."@en ;
    skos:notation "loop-2" .

cmmc:Routine-Manual a cmmc:Routine ;
    rdfs:label "Routine: Manual (human-filed item)"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Marker for MorningReviewItems filed by a human directly (not surfaced by an automated pass). The Phase 2 constrained-write MCP server accepts manual items so the human reviewer can route observations into the same queue alongside Routine-Loop1 and Routine-Loop2 output."@en ;
    skos:notation "manual" .

### =====================================================================
### 5. SKOS CONCEPT SCHEMES (controlled vocabularies)
### =====================================================================
### Per McComb principle 5: separate ontology from taxonomy. Status and
### gapKind values live as SKOS concepts so that adding a new value (e.g.
### a sixth gapKind in a future Phase) does not require an ontology
### version bump — only a SKOS scheme update.

cmmc:GapKindScheme a skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:label "Morning Review Gap Kind Scheme"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Controlled vocabulary for cmmc:gapKind values."@en ;
    skos:hasTopConcept cmmc:GapKind-MissingData ,
                       cmmc:GapKind-OntologyDelta ,
                       cmmc:GapKind-HarnessDelta ,
                       cmmc:GapKind-ElicitationQuestion ,
                       cmmc:GapKind-GateStateChange .

cmmc:GapKind-MissingData a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:GapKindScheme ;
    skos:notation "missing-data" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Missing Data"@en ;
    skos:definition "An Engagement (or other concerned entity) is missing one or more required fields the runtime cannot self-fill. Requires a non-empty cmmc:missingFields list."@en .

cmmc:GapKind-OntologyDelta a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:GapKindScheme ;
    skos:notation "ontology-delta" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Ontology Delta"@en ;
    skos:definition "The CMMC ontology lacks a needed class, property, or invariant. Approval routes to a future /ontogize pass."@en .

cmmc:GapKind-HarnessDelta a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:GapKindScheme ;
    skos:notation "harness-delta" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Harness Delta"@en ;
    skos:definition "The runtime harness (MCP server, routine code, cron config) needs a change. Approval routes to a Phase-2-onwards code/config edit."@en .

cmmc:GapKind-ElicitationQuestion a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:GapKindScheme ;
    skos:notation "elicitation-question" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Elicitation Question"@en ;
    skos:definition "A human SME must answer a question before the Loop can advance. Approval routes to a /elicit session with the named SME target."@en .

cmmc:GapKind-GateStateChange a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:GapKindScheme ;
    skos:notation "gate-state-change" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Gate State Change"@en ;
    skos:definition "A compliance gate query has flipped state since the prior pass (e.g. a contractor moved from Conditional to Final, or a fcaExposureFlag cleared). Surfaced for human awareness, not always action-required."@en .

cmmc:MorningReviewStatusScheme a skos:ConceptScheme ;
    rdfs:label "Morning Review Status Scheme (FSM)"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Controlled vocabulary for cmmc:status values. The four concepts together form a finite state machine; transitions enforced by cmmc:Invariant17 and cmmc:MorningReviewItemShape."@en ;
    skos:hasTopConcept cmmc:Status-Pending ,
                       cmmc:Status-Approved ,
                       cmmc:Status-Rejected ,
                       cmmc:Status-Executed .

cmmc:Status-Pending a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:MorningReviewStatusScheme ;
    skos:notation "pending" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Pending"@en ;
    skos:definition "Default state at creation. Awaiting human review."@en .

cmmc:Status-Approved a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:MorningReviewStatusScheme ;
    skos:notation "approved" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Approved"@en ;
    skos:definition "Human approved the proposal. Awaiting execution by downstream automation. Not terminal."@en .

cmmc:Status-Rejected a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:MorningReviewStatusScheme ;
    skos:notation "rejected" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Rejected"@en ;
    skos:definition "Human declined the proposal. Terminal."@en .

cmmc:Status-Executed a skos:Concept ;
    skos:inScheme cmmc:MorningReviewStatusScheme ;
    skos:notation "executed" ;
    skos:prefLabel "Executed"@en ;
    skos:definition "Approved item has been executed; an Affirmation is attached via cmmc:resolvedBy. Terminal."@en .

### =====================================================================
### 6. INVARIANTS (governance layer — McComb principle 7)
### =====================================================================

cmmc:Invariant17-MorningReviewFSM a cmmc:Invariant ;
    rdfs:label "Morning Review Status FSM"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Status transitions on a MorningReviewItem are restricted to the canonical FSM: pending → approved | rejected; approved → executed. No other transitions are valid. Specifically: rejected and executed are terminal (no outgoing transitions). Backward transitions (e.g. approved → pending, executed → approved) are forbidden. Skip transitions (e.g. pending → executed without intermediate approved) are forbidden. Initial state at creation is always pending. Enforced by cmmc:MorningReviewItemShape (SHACL) and by the Phase 2 constrained-write MCP server, which rejects any write that violates the FSM."@en ;
    cmmc:sourceRef "project_canon_morning_review_queue_phase1.md — Proposed MorningReviewItem shape; Phase 1 prompt invariant 4." .

cmmc:Invariant18-MissingDataRequiresMissingFields a cmmc:Invariant ;
    rdfs:label "Missing-Data Items Require Non-Empty missingFields"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "When cmmc:gapKind='missing-data' on a MorningReviewItem, the item MUST carry a non-empty cmmc:missingFields list AND its cmmc:payload JSON MUST contain a non-empty 'missingFields' array of field names. The two representations (denormalized triples + JSON payload) MUST agree. This guarantees that downstream automation (Phase 3 missing-data scanner) can route every missing-data item to a concrete elicitation target without re-parsing payload shape on every load. Canonical exemplar: ENG-2026-CANON-001 missing-score pattern, with missingFields = [assessedSPRSScore, priorSPRSScore, prohibitedNotMet, poamEligibleCount]."@en ;
    cmmc:sourceRef "project_canon_morning_review_queue_phase1.md — Concrete payload examples for gapKind='missing-data'; Phase 1 prompt 'Don't forget' clause." .

cmmc:Invariant19-MorningReviewItemDefaultPending a cmmc:Invariant ;
    rdfs:label "MorningReviewItem Defaults to Pending at Creation"@en ;
    rdfs:comment "Every newly created MorningReviewItem MUST have cmmc:status='pending'. Direct creation in any other state is forbidden. The Phase 2 constrained-write MCP server enforces this server-side (the create tool ignores any client-supplied status and sets pending unconditionally). The SHACL shape cmmc:MorningReviewItemShape additionally constrains status membership to the four canonical values, so a malformed write fails validation regardless of which state it claims."@en ;
    cmmc:sourceRef "Phase 1 prompt invariant 4: 'every MorningReviewItem MUST have status=pending at creation'." .

### =====================================================================
### 7. SHACL NODESHAPE (runtime enforcement)
### =====================================================================
### Inline SHACL — co-located with the OWL declarations so Phase 2 tooling
### can extract a single shapes file from this delta. The shape encodes:
###   (a) status MUST be one of {pending, approved, rejected, executed}
###   (b) gapKind MUST be one of the five canonical values
###   (c) when gapKind = 'missing-data', missingFields MUST exist with
###       at least one value (sh:qualifiedValueShape pattern)
###   (d) itemId, proposedAt, summary, payload, gapKind, status, targetGraph
###       are all required (minCount 1)
###   (e) proposedBy MUST point to exactly one cmmc:Routine
###
### The FSM transition rule (Invariant 17) cannot be enforced by SHACL
### alone — SHACL validates a single state, not a transition between two
### states. Transition enforcement is the Phase 2 constrained-write MCP
### server's responsibility. The shape catches malformed states; the MCP
### server catches malformed transitions.

cmmc:MorningReviewItemShape a sh:NodeShape ;
    sh:targetClass cmmc:MorningReviewItem ;

    ### Required: itemId (exactly one)
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:itemId ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message "MorningReviewItem requires exactly one itemId."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Required: proposedAt (exactly one)
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:proposedAt ;
        sh:datatype xsd:dateTime ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message "MorningReviewItem requires exactly one proposedAt timestamp."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Required: summary (exactly one)
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:summary ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message "MorningReviewItem requires exactly one one-line summary."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Required: payload (exactly one)
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:payload ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message "MorningReviewItem requires exactly one payload (JSON literal)."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Required: targetGraph (exactly one)
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:targetGraph ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message "MorningReviewItem requires exactly one targetGraph identifier."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Required + value-set: gapKind
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:gapKind ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:in ( "missing-data" "ontology-delta" "harness-delta"
                "elicitation-question" "gate-state-change" ) ;
        sh:message "gapKind must be one of: missing-data, ontology-delta, harness-delta, elicitation-question, gate-state-change."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Required + value-set: status (FSM membership)
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:status ;
        sh:datatype xsd:string ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:in ( "pending" "approved" "rejected" "executed" ) ;
        sh:message "status must be one of: pending, approved, rejected, executed."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Required: proposedBy (exactly one Routine)
    sh:property [
        sh:path cmmc:proposedBy ;
        sh:class cmmc:Routine ;
        sh:minCount 1 ;
        sh:maxCount 1 ;
        sh:message "MorningReviewItem requires exactly one proposing Routine."@en ;
    ] ;

    ### Conditional: when gapKind='missing-data', missingFields must be
    ### non-empty. Encoded as sh:or over two patterns:
    ###   (i)  gapKind != 'missing-data'                       (vacuously satisfied)
    ###   (ii) gapKind = 'missing-data' AND missingFields >= 1
    sh:or (
        [
            sh:path cmmc:gapKind ;
            sh:not [ sh:hasValue "missing-data" ]
        ]
        [
            sh:path cmmc:missingFields ;
            sh:minCount 1 ;
            sh:message "When gapKind='missing-data', cmmc:missingFields MUST contain at least one field name (Invariant 18)."@en ;
        ]
    ) ;

    sh:message "MorningReviewItem violates v0.4.4 invariants — see specific property violations above."@en .

### =====================================================================
### END v0.4.4 DELTA PATCH
### =====================================================================

### END OF ONTOLOGY v0.4.4 ###
